Ahhhhh !

02:38.171 --> 02:40.765
[ Bird caws ]

02:40.841 --> 02:45.869
Ahhh ! Ahhh ! Ahhhh !

02:45.946 --> 02:48.574
<i>[ Growling ]</i>

02:48.648 --> 02:50.411
[ Leaves rustling ]

02:50.484 --> 02:54.011
Ahhhh ! Ahhh !

02:54.087 --> 02:57.215
<i>[ Growling ]</i>

02:57.290 --> 02:59.690
Ahhh ! Ahhhhh !

02:59.759 --> 03:02.728
<i>[ Roaring ]</i>

03:02.796 --> 03:04.229
Ahhhhhh !

03:04.297 --> 03:06.663
<i>Man: Grab him!</i>
<i>Grab him, Judas! Take him!</i>

03:06.733 --> 03:09.031
We got the monster
that wants to hack up
our children .

03:09.102 --> 03:11.070
<i>Get the chains on him.</i>

03:11.137 --> 03:13.071
-- l got him .
-- [ Chains rattling ]

03:13.139 --> 03:17.303
<i>Man:</i>
<i>The ancient evil has followed</i>
<i>us here to this new world.</i>

03:17.377 --> 03:19.675
<i>He has stolen our children</i>

03:19.746 --> 03:22.977
<i>and tried to resurrect</i>
<i>his wicked race.</i>

03:23.049 --> 03:26.951
<i>But we, in our righteousness,</i>
<i>have prevailed.</i>

03:27.020 --> 03:30.114
[ Voice breaking ]
My babies -- he took
my babies!

03:30.190 --> 03:32.454
And here he shall be buried ,

03:32.526 --> 03:35.893
and this oak tree
will seal his fate.

03:35.962 --> 03:42.424
lts roots will be his prison ,
which must never be disturbed .

03:42.502 --> 03:44.800
[ Growling ]
Hear me, Phineas Worrell .

03:44.871 --> 03:47.339
<i>When the face of death</i>
<i>covers the moon,</i>

03:47.407 --> 03:51.605
<i>one with your blood</i>
<i>in his veins will release me,</i>

03:51.678 --> 03:54.408
<i>and victory will at last</i>
<i>be mine!</i>

03:54.481 --> 03:55.641
[ Crowd screams ]

03:55.715 --> 03:57.649
[ Crying ]
There, there, Francis.

03:57.717 --> 04:00.515
We'll get them back.
You'll see.

04:00.587 --> 04:03.852
l banish you
to eternal darkness.

04:05.926 --> 04:08.622
<i>Girl: ''So in the hours</i>
<i>just before midnight,</i>

04:08.695 --> 04:11.687
<i>''the people of Briarville</i>
<i>buried Trantor the Troll</i>

04:11.765 --> 04:15.531
''in the cold , damp ground .

04:15.602 --> 04:16.863
The end .''

04:16.937 --> 04:18.267
Thank you , Elizabeth .

04:18.338 --> 04:21.000
Class, what did you think
of her report?

04:21.074 --> 04:22.166
That's bull !

04:22.242 --> 04:23.436
<i>lt's not bull!</i>

04:23.510 --> 04:25.341
l read it in a book.

04:25.412 --> 04:26.674
Yeah , it was a cool report.

04:26.746 --> 04:28.304
lt probably just went over
your head .

04:28.381 --> 04:30.906
The reports were
supposed to be on the
history of the town ,

04:30.984 --> 04:32.474
not ''Nightmare
on Troll Street.''

04:32.552 --> 04:33.484
[ Laughter ]

04:33.553 --> 04:35.544
Now, settle down , class.

04:35.622 --> 04:36.850
Lay off her, Murdock.

04:36.923 --> 04:38.390
What are you gonna do
about it, runt?

04:38.458 --> 04:42.053
Elizabeth scared Kenny
with a spooky story.

04:42.128 --> 04:43.789
The dork likes her.

04:43.863 --> 04:47.060
<i>Although Elizabeth's report was</i>
<i>a bit unusual,</i>

04:47.133 --> 04:50.068
legends and myths are
a real part of history,

04:50.136 --> 04:53.799
especially here in Briarville,
with our unique past.

04:53.873 --> 04:55.500
<i>l think it was a clever idea.</i>

04:55.575 --> 04:56.507
<i>Woman: Ernest!</i>

04:56.576 --> 04:59.807
<i>Ernest!</i>
<i>Stop the truck!</i>

04:59.879 --> 05:01.471
[ Engine revving , dog barking ]

05:01.548 --> 05:03.948
So, uh , Elizabeth ,

05:04.017 --> 05:06.815
what was the curse
the troll put on Phineas?

05:06.886 --> 05:10.515
Well , legend has it
that from that moment on ,

05:10.590 --> 05:16.551
Phineas' descendants would
get dumber and dumber. . .

05:16.630 --> 05:19.098
<i>and dumber.</i>

05:19.165 --> 05:21.360
[ Motor running ]

05:21.434 --> 05:23.026
[ Water splashing ]

05:23.103 --> 05:26.038
Yeah , when they hired me
as sanitary engineer,

05:26.106 --> 05:30.167
they had no idea that l was
actually Ernest P. Worrell ,

05:30.243 --> 05:33.235
man of destiny,
ruler of refuse,

05:33.313 --> 05:36.510
a man who has taken dominion
over his environment. . .

05:36.583 --> 05:37.515
[ Click ]

05:37.584 --> 05:39.074
<i>...a brilliant innovator</i>

05:39.152 --> 05:41.712
<i>in the fertile field</i>
<i>of recycling.</i>

05:41.788 --> 05:44.416
The czar of jars,
the baron of bottles,

05:44.491 --> 05:46.356
the duke of dust --

05:46.426 --> 05:47.518
[ Thud ]

05:47.594 --> 05:49.585
[ Machine whirring ]

05:49.663 --> 05:50.595
Oh , no!

05:50.664 --> 05:52.632
Uh , the switch is on the fritz!

05:52.699 --> 05:55.429
<i>Uh, Rimshot! Rimshot!</i>
<i>A little help here, Rimshot!</i>

05:55.502 --> 05:57.697
Rimshot!
Rimshot, the clutch !

05:57.771 --> 05:58.897
[ Barking ]

05:58.972 --> 06:01.270
Rimshot, the clutch !
The clutch !

06:02.976 --> 06:04.603
The clutch , Rimshot!

06:04.678 --> 06:05.872
Help!

06:05.945 --> 06:07.537
<i>Rimshot, the clutch!</i>

06:07.614 --> 06:09.741
[ Whirring ]

06:09.816 --> 06:11.613
<i>Rimshot! Whoa!</i>

06:11.685 --> 06:12.674
Wa-aaaah !

06:12.752 --> 06:14.549
[ Thud ]

06:14.621 --> 06:17.920
[ Paper rustling ]

06:17.991 --> 06:19.959
Ahh .

06:22.128 --> 06:23.561
That was close.

06:23.630 --> 06:24.562
[ Clicking ]

06:24.631 --> 06:26.428
[ Hissing ]

06:26.499 --> 06:27.591
[ Thud ]

06:27.667 --> 06:31.501
Oh . . .
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:31.571 --> 06:33.766
[ Clicking ]

06:37.310 --> 06:39.403
<i>l'm gonna be squooshed!</i>

06:39.479 --> 06:42.141
[ Gears clicking ]

06:46.753 --> 06:49.517
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

06:49.589 --> 06:51.750
[ Metal creaking ]

06:58.598 --> 07:00.657
[ Rimshot barking ]

07:00.734 --> 07:02.326
[ Grunting ]

07:02.402 --> 07:03.699
[ Snap ]

07:03.770 --> 07:06.864
<i>Rimshot, help!</i>
<i>Do something! Rimshot!</i>

07:06.940 --> 07:08.305
[ Horn honking ]

07:08.374 --> 07:10.535
Aah ! Aah !

07:12.946 --> 07:16.074
<i>[ High-pitched voice ]</i>
<i>No, no! Don't stick my head</i>
<i>in those gears!</i>

07:16.149 --> 07:17.980
[ Normal voice ]
But i-it's me or you !

07:18.051 --> 07:21.043
[ High-pitched voice ]
But l have a family at
the doll factory!

07:21.121 --> 07:23.180
[ Normal voice ]
l'll send them a nice card .

07:23.256 --> 07:26.589
[ High-pitched voice ]
You'll never get away with this,
Ernest! l know where you live!

07:26.659 --> 07:29.287
[ Crunching , rumbling ]

07:29.362 --> 07:31.956
[ Gasping ]

07:32.031 --> 07:33.623
[ Barking ]

07:33.700 --> 07:35.861
[ Horn honking ]

07:35.935 --> 07:38.460
[ Mumbling ]

07:38.538 --> 07:40.733
[ Rumbling ]

07:45.345 --> 07:46.937
[ Rumbling stops ]

07:47.013 --> 07:48.776
Ah heh heh heh heh heh .

07:48.848 --> 07:51.715
[ Electricity crackling ]

07:51.785 --> 07:53.218
Wa-ahhhh !

07:53.286 --> 07:55.254
[ Machine whirring ]

07:55.321 --> 07:57.755
Those Murdocks are
major jerks.

07:57.824 --> 08:00.349
lf their lQ's were any lower,
they'd be plants.

08:00.426 --> 08:02.894
<i>[ Barking ]</i>

08:02.962 --> 08:05.430
Rimshot!
Something's wrong !

08:05.498 --> 08:07.830
<i>Ernest: [ Muffled ]</i>
<i>Help! Let me out of here!</i>

08:07.901 --> 08:09.027
[ Banging ]

08:09.102 --> 08:10.865
-- Ernest!
-- [ Rimshot barks ]

08:10.937 --> 08:12.529
[ Ernest shouting indistinctly ]

08:12.605 --> 08:14.095
This should open it.

08:14.174 --> 08:15.766
[ Rimshot barking ]

08:15.842 --> 08:17.776
Way to go!
You did it!

08:17.844 --> 08:20.870
[ lmitating John Wayne ]
Well , no need to thank me,
little lady.

08:20.947 --> 08:22.710
Just some
routine hero work.

08:22.782 --> 08:25.182
[ Babbling ]

08:25.251 --> 08:27.378
[ Mechanical whirring ]

08:27.453 --> 08:28.385
Aahhh !

08:28.454 --> 08:32.015
[ Thud , Ernest groaning ]

08:33.092 --> 08:34.855
[ Vehicles passing ]

08:38.231 --> 08:39.994
[ Engine turns off ]

08:40.066 --> 08:43.832
Sheriff. . .

08:43.903 --> 08:46.929
l've just come
from the Hackmore place.

08:47.006 --> 08:48.268
lt's an absolute mess.

08:48.341 --> 08:50.138
lt violates every code
in the book.

08:50.210 --> 08:52.770
l want it cleaned up,
and l want it cleaned up
immediately.

08:52.846 --> 08:56.338
Yes. Well , mayor, l served
the papers, and Ernest said
he would get right on it.

08:56.416 --> 08:58.475
lf he can't handle it,
you fire him .

08:58.551 --> 08:59.813
Yes, sir.

08:59.886 --> 09:01.877
There goes that idiot
now.

09:01.955 --> 09:05.391
Ha. And he's going <i>away</i>
from the Hackmore place.

09:05.458 --> 09:07.722
That was close.

09:07.794 --> 09:11.753
Yeah , my dad said
we can get in big trouble
riding in here.

09:11.831 --> 09:13.992
Well , it is against
city regulations and all ,

09:14.067 --> 09:16.126
but as driver
of a garbage truck,

09:16.202 --> 09:18.363
l feel like captain
of my own ship,

09:18.438 --> 09:21.874
master of my own fate,
able to make my own rules,

09:21.941 --> 09:23.875
a man above the law.

09:23.943 --> 09:26.935
[ Siren wailing ]

09:27.013 --> 09:28.105
Uh-oh .

09:28.181 --> 09:30.479
lt's my dad !

09:30.550 --> 09:31.983
[ Siren stops ]

09:32.051 --> 09:33.985
[ Truck brakes hiss ]

09:34.053 --> 09:36.544
[ Engine turns off ]

09:40.894 --> 09:42.361
[ Truck door closes ]

09:42.428 --> 09:43.986
Uh , was l speeding?

09:44.063 --> 09:47.157
Sometimes the raw power
of this vehicle just gets
away from me --

09:47.233 --> 09:50.066
Ernest, l told you
to get out to the
Hackmore place --

09:50.136 --> 09:51.068
Kenny: Shh !

09:51.137 --> 09:52.502
You two --

09:52.572 --> 09:54.335
get out of there and
get in the car right now.

09:54.407 --> 09:55.601
Dad , l --

09:55.675 --> 09:57.802
No, l don't want to hear it.
Get in the car.

09:57.877 --> 10:00.175
<i>lt wasn't their fault.</i>
<i>l-l'm the captain, and</i> --

10:00.246 --> 10:02.737
No, look,
l told you to get out
to the Hackmore place

10:02.815 --> 10:04.806
and clean it up,
and you haven't done it.

10:04.884 --> 10:06.943
Well , uh , l don't have
a toxic-waste permit.

10:07.020 --> 10:10.820
Uh , l just took a cold pill ,
and l'm not supposed to operate
heavy machinery.

10:10.890 --> 10:13.484
<i>Look, if you want to</i>
<i>hang on to your job,</i>

10:13.559 --> 10:15.789
you'll get out there
and do it.

10:15.862 --> 10:17.454
See you , Ernest.

10:17.530 --> 10:19.395
[ Sighs ]

10:21.401 --> 10:23.801
[ Hinges squeak, thud ]

10:23.870 --> 10:26.134
[ Birds chirping ]

10:26.205 --> 10:28.139
[ Crow caws ]

10:28.207 --> 10:29.799
[ Squeaking ]

10:29.876 --> 10:33.312
[ Vehicle approaches,
brakes hiss ]

10:33.379 --> 10:36.314
[ Engine turns off ]

10:36.382 --> 10:37.974
[ Crow caws ]

10:38.051 --> 10:42.488
[ Truck door opens, closes ]

10:44.724 --> 10:47.818
[ Rimshot barking ]

10:47.894 --> 10:49.225
Come on , boy.

10:49.295 --> 10:51.559
We've nothing to fear
but fear itself,

10:51.631 --> 10:52.723
plus the known fact

10:52.799 --> 10:54.733
that Old Lady Hackmore
will turn us into

10:54.801 --> 10:57.292
a couple of drooling ,
red-eyed zombies

10:57.370 --> 10:58.632
if she catches us here.

10:58.705 --> 11:00.696
[ Rimshot barks ]

11:03.176 --> 11:05.110
[ Crow caws ]

11:05.178 --> 11:07.169
[ Organ plays ]

11:12.452 --> 11:13.714
[ Rattling ]

11:13.786 --> 11:15.219
Well , nobody home.

11:15.288 --> 11:17.085
l guess they're out
robbin' graves

11:17.156 --> 11:20.125
or bitin' the heads off chickens
or whatever's in voodoo vogue.

11:20.193 --> 11:22.923
Get off of my property!

11:22.996 --> 11:24.759
<i>What are you</i>
<i>doing here?!</i>

11:24.831 --> 11:27.527
Ma'am , l'm just here to
pick up all this garbage.

11:27.600 --> 11:30.000
Got no garbage here,

11:30.069 --> 11:32.765
only the expressions
of the soul .

11:32.839 --> 11:35.103
Uh , ma'am , l'm
an official representative

11:35.174 --> 11:37.108
of the Briarville
city government,

11:37.176 --> 11:39.838
<i>and, incidentally,</i>
<i>a close personal friend</i>
<i>of Mayor Murdock's.</i>

11:39.912 --> 11:42.039
Aren't you
that Worrell kid?

11:42.115 --> 11:43.980
-- [ Bird caws ]
-- Yes, ma'am .
-- <i>[ Gasps ]</i>

11:44.050 --> 11:48.612
Oh . . .you will bring down
the curse on us all !

11:48.688 --> 11:51.350
Woe to you ,
oh , ye seed of Worrell .

11:51.424 --> 11:53.483
Get out of here
and don't come back!

11:53.559 --> 11:55.151
l wish you'd reconsider.

11:55.228 --> 11:58.026
Recycling is a. . .
a very important part
of good citizenship.

11:58.097 --> 11:59.064
<i>Yeah.</i>

11:59.132 --> 12:01.066
And you'll be
a dead citizen .

12:01.134 --> 12:03.932
When the poisons of
the evil courses through

12:04.003 --> 12:06.471
the portals and channels
of your body,

12:06.539 --> 12:10.475
you will lie
a quivering , toxic mass
of screaming flesh !

12:10.543 --> 12:11.976
They will have to load you

12:12.045 --> 12:14.138
and the rest
of this backward town

12:14.213 --> 12:16.579
on a meat wagon
with a pitchfork!

12:16.649 --> 12:18.480
So in other words,

12:18.551 --> 12:20.951
it might be better
if l came back another day.

12:21.020 --> 12:22.453
Aahhhhh !

12:22.522 --> 12:24.319
[ Flames roaring ]

12:24.390 --> 12:28.258
Ahhhhhhhh !

12:28.327 --> 12:30.261
Pretty scary scream ,
huh?

12:30.329 --> 12:31.990
My heart
was in my throat.

12:32.065 --> 12:33.396
You have a rare gift.

12:33.466 --> 12:35.434
You haven't seen
the grand finale yet.

12:35.501 --> 12:36.433
Come here.

12:36.502 --> 12:37.764
[ Hinges squeak ]

12:37.837 --> 12:40.431
See, they'll come in here
and go through that door

12:40.506 --> 12:43.532
<i>and up this way, where</i>
<i>Joey hits 'em in the face</i>
<i>with a mop.</i>

12:43.609 --> 12:45.099
A <i>wet</i> mop.

12:45.178 --> 12:47.738
Then they'll have to crawl
through all these peeled grapes

12:47.814 --> 12:49.873
while l'm screaming ,
''Where are my eyes?

12:49.949 --> 12:51.439
Don't step on
my eyeballs!''

12:51.517 --> 12:53.508
Gross!
But l love it.

12:53.586 --> 12:55.019
[ Rumbling ]

12:55.088 --> 12:56.521
lt's the Murdocks!

12:56.589 --> 12:58.682
Look out, witch !
lt's an earthquake!

12:58.758 --> 13:00.988
lt's a big one --
5.3 on the Richter scale!

13:01.060 --> 13:02.652
Quick!
Let's run out the back!

13:02.728 --> 13:04.628
lt's caving in !
lt's caving in !

13:04.697 --> 13:05.823
Get out!
You're gonna die!

13:05.898 --> 13:07.832
We're caving in !

13:07.900 --> 13:10.061
Let's run for it!
Go! Go!

13:10.136 --> 13:13.503
[ Wood cracking ]

13:13.573 --> 13:16.565
You buttheads made
a big mistake!

13:18.211 --> 13:20.509
[ Thud ]

13:20.580 --> 13:22.377
Hey, where do you think
you're going?

13:22.448 --> 13:24.245
The fun's just beginning !

13:24.317 --> 13:27.411
<i>l don't know what to do.</i>
<i>They wrecked our haunted house.</i>

13:27.487 --> 13:30.285
They -- they wrecked
your haunted house?

13:30.356 --> 13:31.550
Yeah .

13:31.624 --> 13:33.251
You know, what you need
is some of that

13:33.326 --> 13:35.260
hysterical perspective,
know what l mean?

13:35.328 --> 13:37.660
Not. . .really.

13:37.730 --> 13:40.563
[ Straining ]
You need to learn
a self-defense lesson

13:40.633 --> 13:42.863
from . . .tiny Botswana,
that. . .

13:42.935 --> 13:45.335
plucky little nation
that defeated the. . .

13:45.404 --> 13:47.531
[ Straining ]
giant Ottoman Empire.

13:47.607 --> 13:49.074
[ Grunts ]

13:49.142 --> 13:51.337
Ernest, what does that
have to do with me?

13:51.410 --> 13:53.207
l'm glad you asked .

13:53.279 --> 13:55.679
[ Grunts ]

13:55.748 --> 13:58.182
[ British accent ] lt was a dark
night in lower Botswana.

13:58.251 --> 14:01.186
Giant bula bula flies droned
in the still air.

14:01.254 --> 14:02.380
Then it came --

14:02.455 --> 14:05.253
the screeching war cry
of the Ottoman hordes.

14:05.324 --> 14:07.019
Wa-aah !

14:07.093 --> 14:09.618
We're the Ottomans,
and you're not!

14:09.695 --> 14:12.095
You're in a world of it now,
pal !

14:12.165 --> 14:14.429
Oh , my. l'm afraid .

14:14.500 --> 14:15.592
Sure, l'm scared .

14:15.668 --> 14:17.863
E-everybody in Botswana's
scared .

14:17.937 --> 14:19.370
lt looks like curtains.

14:19.438 --> 14:22.202
This place is just screaming
for drapes.

14:22.275 --> 14:25.472
Don't worry about the Ottomans.
They're just wussies.

14:25.545 --> 14:26.477
They're all talk.

14:26.546 --> 14:29.106
l knew an Ottoman eagle scout.

14:29.182 --> 14:31.912
He got a merit badge
in wholesale slaughter.

14:31.984 --> 14:33.281
Aah !

14:33.352 --> 14:35.217
Come on , Ottomans!
Take a piece of me!

14:35.288 --> 14:36.380
[ Rimshot barking ]

14:36.455 --> 14:39.322
What we need . . .is
the high ground .

14:39.392 --> 14:42.088
The high ground is no good
without trees.

14:42.161 --> 14:46.427
Friends, Romans, Botswanians,
lend me your tree.

14:46.499 --> 14:48.091
There ain't no trees
in Botswana.

14:48.167 --> 14:49.759
Unh-unh . l know.

14:49.835 --> 14:52.770
l am a Botswanian lumberjack,
and l ain't never had a job.

14:52.838 --> 14:54.635
We need dress shields.

14:54.707 --> 14:57.471
You need the high ground
to keep away from us

14:57.543 --> 15:00.068
'cause. . .
'Cause we're the Ottomans!

15:00.146 --> 15:02.080
Aah !

15:02.148 --> 15:05.208
Ernest, l know! l know!
What we need is. . .

15:05.284 --> 15:06.774
a treehouse!

15:06.852 --> 15:09.650
l thought we needed
dress shields.

15:09.722 --> 15:11.189
[ Creaking ]

15:11.257 --> 15:14.317
[ Whoosh ]

15:14.393 --> 15:16.987
[ Glass shatters ]

15:18.764 --> 15:20.527
Ernest!

15:20.600 --> 15:23.296
Direct hit.
Way to go, Ernest.

15:23.369 --> 15:25.200
Do you smell fish?

15:26.806 --> 15:28.831
The first step
in treehouse construction ,

15:28.908 --> 15:30.671
which l'll refer to
as ''step one,''

15:30.743 --> 15:32.176
is tree selection .

15:32.245 --> 15:33.678
With the right tree,

15:33.746 --> 15:36.180
we can build
an impregnant fortress

15:36.249 --> 15:39.343
armed with nuclear rays,
disintegrator beams,

15:39.418 --> 15:42.012
and all the latest
electronic technology

15:42.088 --> 15:45.489
to afford us a safe haven
against advancing hordes

15:45.558 --> 15:49.085
as well as offering
truly elegant country living

15:49.161 --> 15:51.356
in rustic surroundings.

15:52.865 --> 15:54.799
[ Echoing ]

15:54.867 --> 15:57.335
Nah .
Too much bass.

15:57.403 --> 15:58.995
[ Solid sound ]

15:59.071 --> 16:00.333
This one's nice.

16:00.406 --> 16:02.670
[ Creaking , thud ]

16:02.742 --> 16:04.710
Ah heh . Too many
termites. Ah heh .

16:04.777 --> 16:06.210
This looks like
a good one.

16:06.279 --> 16:07.371
[ Bird caws ]

16:07.446 --> 16:08.879
[ Feathers rustling ]

16:08.948 --> 16:10.040
lnhabited .

16:10.116 --> 16:12.050
Oh , jeez. [ Coughs ]

16:12.118 --> 16:15.713
What's the big idea?
A tree is a tree.

16:15.788 --> 16:18.951
We've got to find one
big enough to keep
the Ottomans out.

16:19.025 --> 16:20.287
The Ottomans?

16:20.359 --> 16:21.621
Don't ask.

16:21.694 --> 16:26.529
<i>Oo-o-o-o-o-o-h!</i>

16:26.599 --> 16:28.692
This is neat!

16:28.768 --> 16:30.599
[ Bird cawing ]

16:40.980 --> 16:42.140
Go on !

16:44.317 --> 16:47.753
lt's okay.
Go on !

16:47.820 --> 16:50.448
Go on !

16:50.523 --> 16:53.686
[ Birds cawing and whistling ]

16:53.759 --> 16:55.351
l don't like this.

16:55.428 --> 16:58.022
Well , l didn't see
any poison ivy.

16:58.097 --> 16:59.689
The worst thing
that could happen

16:59.765 --> 17:02.359
would be Dutch elm blight,
and none of us are Dutch .

17:02.435 --> 17:04.561
[ Birds snorting and cawing ]

17:04.637 --> 17:08.436
[ Owl hooting ,
woodpecker pecking ]

17:08.507 --> 17:11.601
[ Bird cawing ]

17:11.676 --> 17:15.306
Remember, if any of us
get separated ,

17:15.381 --> 17:18.281
there's an old pioneer way
of finding north --

17:18.351 --> 17:22.617
the bark always grows
on the outside of a tree.

17:22.688 --> 17:24.315
<i>Elizabeth:</i>
<i>ls he serious?</i>

17:24.390 --> 17:26.550
<i>Kenny:</i>
<i>l'm afraid so.</i>

17:26.625 --> 17:28.387
<i>This is it!</i>

17:28.461 --> 17:31.328
The foundation
of the high ground --

17:31.397 --> 17:32.796
tree of the stars!

17:32.865 --> 17:35.299
This is a tree
to die for.

17:35.368 --> 17:38.963
[ Bird caws, Rimshot barks ]

17:39.038 --> 17:41.268
<i>Ernest: Come on, kids.</i>
<i>This'll be fun.</i>

17:41.340 --> 17:44.104
<i>l've been collecting</i>
<i>this stuff for years.</i>

17:44.176 --> 17:47.270
Well , l guess we got to
give it a try.

17:47.346 --> 17:49.177
No guts, no glory.

17:53.052 --> 17:58.615
Yes, just as the journey
of 1 ,000 miles begins
with a single step,

17:58.691 --> 18:01.785
a treehouse begins
with a single nail .

18:01.861 --> 18:03.123
Observe.

18:03.195 --> 18:04.628
[ Slurp ]

18:04.697 --> 18:06.790
[ Bird caws ]

18:06.866 --> 18:08.458
[ Hammer pounding ]

18:08.534 --> 18:11.594
<i>Man: Here he shall be buried,</i>

18:11.670 --> 18:15.197
<i>and this oak tree will seal</i>
<i>his fate.</i>

18:15.274 --> 18:18.869
<i>lts roots will be his prison,</i>

18:18.944 --> 18:22.209
<i>which must never be disturbed.</i>

18:22.281 --> 18:23.407
[ Rumbling ]

18:23.482 --> 18:27.145
<i>Return this evil</i>
<i>from whence it came.</i>

18:27.219 --> 18:30.711
[ Growling ]

18:32.725 --> 18:35.489
Ahhhhh !

18:35.561 --> 18:39.554
[ Growling , barking ]

18:47.573 --> 18:50.201
One treehouse --
under construction .

18:50.276 --> 18:51.573
<i>Joey: Crank 'er up.</i>

18:51.644 --> 18:52.838
[ Saw cutting ]

18:52.912 --> 18:56.177
<i>All right.</i>
<i>This is really working.</i>

18:56.248 --> 18:58.182
[ Motor whirring ]

18:58.250 --> 19:00.514
<i>This is great!</i>

19:07.493 --> 19:09.723
[ Bird caws ]

19:09.795 --> 19:12.195
<i>All right, Joey.</i>
<i>Over here.</i>

19:14.066 --> 19:16.227
-- <i>Another wall coming up.</i>
-- <i>Good work.</i>

19:16.302 --> 19:19.032
<i>Elizabeth:</i>
<i>One more side to go.</i>

19:19.104 --> 19:21.265
This is really looking
great.

19:21.340 --> 19:23.934
[ Bird caws ]

19:24.009 --> 19:27.410
The spirits are loose again .
Who would dare enter here?

19:27.480 --> 19:29.038
[ Crow caws ]

19:29.114 --> 19:30.604
--All right! We did it!
-- Yeah !

19:30.683 --> 19:32.207
This is really neat.

19:32.284 --> 19:34.149
This is your high ground .

19:34.220 --> 19:36.381
<i>Old Lady Hackmore: [ Gasps ]</i>
<i>l felt it! l felt it!</i>

19:36.455 --> 19:37.888
<i>Heaven help us!</i>

19:37.957 --> 19:39.788
<i>The signs showed me</i> --

19:39.859 --> 19:42.623
<i>the sun,</i>
<i>the moon, the stars</i> --

19:42.695 --> 19:45.425
oh , horror will once more
walk among us.

19:45.498 --> 19:47.966
The nightmare will begin
again .

19:48.033 --> 19:49.864
[ Sobs ]

19:49.935 --> 19:52.199
Well , it's not the greatest
treehouse in the world ,

19:52.271 --> 19:54.136
but l wouldn't call it
a nightmare, either.

19:54.206 --> 19:55.639
-- Worrell !
-- [ Bird caws ]

19:55.708 --> 19:58.302
What have you done?!
What have you done to the tree?

19:58.377 --> 20:02.211
A whole world of trees,
and you had to pick this one!

20:02.281 --> 20:05.717
Well , we didn't know this was
your land , or we would've asked
if it was okay.

20:05.784 --> 20:10.050
lt will open
the ancient door and
all that lurks inside!

20:10.122 --> 20:11.384
Flee this evil place!

20:11.457 --> 20:13.152
-- Flee!
-- [ Bird caws ]

20:13.225 --> 20:14.658
<i>Old Lady Hackmore!</i>

20:14.727 --> 20:17.787
Wow! l thought she never
went out of her house.

20:17.863 --> 20:20.263
Probably some simple
misunderstanding .

20:20.332 --> 20:22.926
Maybe l should go
and have a talk with her.

20:23.002 --> 20:25.937
[ Floorboards creaking ]

20:26.005 --> 20:27.529
They will return . . .

20:27.606 --> 20:29.233
<i>Well, wait a minute.</i>
<i>Wait a minute.</i>

20:29.308 --> 20:31.640
We're not really <i>on</i> your place,
more like <i>above</i> it.

20:31.710 --> 20:34.144
-- Couldn't we talk air rights?
-- Get away. Get away.

20:34.213 --> 20:35.305
[ Bird caws ]

20:35.381 --> 20:38.145
-- That was spooky.
-- Yeah .

20:38.217 --> 20:41.277
Come on . l think
they went this way.

20:41.353 --> 20:43.844
Yeah . They got to be
around here somewhere.

20:43.923 --> 20:45.891
[ Bird caws ]

20:45.958 --> 20:47.448
lt's the Murdocks!

20:47.526 --> 20:49.118
All right.
Battle stations.

20:49.194 --> 20:51.924
Let's see how this baby
works under actual
field conditions!

20:51.997 --> 20:52.929
Let's go!

20:52.998 --> 20:54.989
Time to get even .

20:55.067 --> 20:57.535
Tearing up this place
will be major fun .

20:57.603 --> 20:59.594
Yeah . l wonder
where the wimps are.

20:59.672 --> 21:00.934
[ Clattering ]

21:01.006 --> 21:02.564
-- Get down !
-- Watch this!

21:02.641 --> 21:03.801
[ Rattling ]

21:06.579 --> 21:07.637
[ Clicking ]

21:07.713 --> 21:10.181
l've got 'em in my sights. . .

21:10.249 --> 21:11.978
lock and load . . .

21:12.051 --> 21:14.019
and . . .fire.

21:14.086 --> 21:15.417
Both : Aah !

21:16.155 --> 21:18.020
[ Grunts ]

21:18.090 --> 21:19.352
Load me up.

21:19.425 --> 21:21.620
Ammunition coming in --
pepperoni and cheese.

21:21.694 --> 21:24.185
<i>More ammo, Rimshot.</i>
<i>Good boy!</i>

21:24.263 --> 21:25.525
-- Let's go!
-- [ Bell rings ]

21:25.598 --> 21:27.361
[ Whoosh ]

21:27.433 --> 21:28.365
Fire.

21:28.434 --> 21:29.992
[ Thud , splat ]

21:30.069 --> 21:32.264
-- [ Clicking ]
-- Fire three! Got him !

21:32.338 --> 21:33.930
Bingo!

21:34.006 --> 21:35.132
Chicken liver comin' up.

21:35.207 --> 21:36.765
-- Now!
-- [ Bell rings ]

21:36.842 --> 21:37.774
<i>Way to go, Joey!</i>

21:37.843 --> 21:38.867
Ugh !

21:38.944 --> 21:40.343
-- [ Bell rings ]
-- <i>That's delivery, boys!</i>

21:40.412 --> 21:42.312
-- Aah !
-- [ Laughs ]

21:42.381 --> 21:43.313
Aah !

21:43.382 --> 21:44.508
Direct hit!

21:44.583 --> 21:46.551
Ew! A pizza mess!

21:46.619 --> 21:49.679
Binder, this isn't
the end of this!

21:51.624 --> 21:52.613
Yeah .

21:52.691 --> 21:54.124
They're on the run !

21:54.193 --> 21:55.956
And no collateral damage,
either.

21:56.028 --> 21:57.586
All right!
That was great!

21:59.231 --> 22:02.723
[ Crickets chirp,
owl hoots ]

22:02.801 --> 22:04.393
[ Footsteps approaching ]

22:04.470 --> 22:05.562
Halt! Who goes there?

22:05.638 --> 22:07.833
Uh , don't shoot.
Don't shoot.

22:07.906 --> 22:09.203
l'm on your side.

22:09.274 --> 22:11.970
Sorry, Ernest. l guess
we're still a little bit jumpy.

22:12.044 --> 22:13.477
<i>Elizabeth:</i>
<i>Guess what happened.</i>

22:13.545 --> 22:15.012
The Murdocks came by.

22:15.080 --> 22:17.344
But they never had
a chance.

22:17.416 --> 22:19.816
Yeah , and the Botswanians
kicked butt.

22:19.885 --> 22:21.284
Told you .

22:21.353 --> 22:24.811
Hey, Ernest, what was
Mrs. Hackmore going on about?

22:24.890 --> 22:27.882
Oh , she still believes in
trolls and magic spells

22:27.960 --> 22:29.393
and things like that.

22:29.461 --> 22:32.396
Trolls? Like hide under bridges
and eat little girls?

22:32.464 --> 22:34.091
Cut it out, dork.

22:34.166 --> 22:36.396
lt's like the legend
of Trantor.

22:36.468 --> 22:38.095
Elizabeth , get a life.

22:38.170 --> 22:40.001
Just because you write
a report about it

22:40.072 --> 22:41.903
doesn't mean it comes true.

22:41.974 --> 22:45.375
She told me about this troll
that had red , glowing eyes

22:45.444 --> 22:47.036
and walks like this.

22:47.112 --> 22:48.545
[ Grumbling ]

22:48.614 --> 22:50.275
[ Laughing ]

22:50.349 --> 22:51.782
And if he ever gets loose,

22:51.850 --> 22:54.114
he'll go after
the children first.

22:54.186 --> 22:57.280
And he turns them into
little wooden dolls,

22:57.356 --> 22:59.449
which gives him his power.

22:59.525 --> 23:04.485
And that ugly little rascal
is still alive. . .

23:04.563 --> 23:06.997
down there.

23:07.066 --> 23:08.328
-- But. . .
-- [ All gasp ]

23:08.400 --> 23:09.924
He can
only be awakened

23:10.002 --> 23:12.470
on the night
before Halloween . . .

23:12.538 --> 23:14.403
Like tonight.

23:14.473 --> 23:15.872
. . .when a Worrell . . .

23:15.941 --> 23:17.704
Like you .

23:18.777 --> 23:23.680
. . .places his hand on a tree --
like this -- and says,

23:23.749 --> 23:28.618
[ Low-pitched voice ] ''Yea,
l call thee forth , Trantor.''

23:28.687 --> 23:31.281
[ Knocks three times ]

23:31.356 --> 23:33.586
[ Normal voice ]
But what are the chances
of that happening?

23:33.659 --> 23:36.150
[ Roots cracking ]

23:41.867 --> 23:43.835
[ Growling ]

23:53.212 --> 23:56.477
[ Growling ]

23:56.548 --> 23:57.776
[ Thunder crashes ]

23:57.850 --> 23:58.839
Looks like some rain !

23:58.917 --> 24:00.077
Wouldn't be safe here!

24:00.152 --> 24:03.610
Uh , hey, wait a minute, fellas.
Wait. Hold on .

24:03.689 --> 24:05.054
Hey, guys, wait for me!

24:05.124 --> 24:06.421
Hurry, Elizabeth !
Hurry!

24:06.492 --> 24:07.618
Let's go!

24:07.693 --> 24:09.354
<i>Hey, everybody,</i>
<i>where are you going?</i>

24:09.428 --> 24:11.487
<i>Can't you see l'm up here</i>
<i>all...</i>

24:11.563 --> 24:13.428
Alone?

24:13.499 --> 24:15.490
[ Rattling ]

24:15.567 --> 24:17.159
[ Rimshot barks ]

24:17.236 --> 24:18.828
Easy, Rimshot.

24:18.904 --> 24:20.735
Easy, boy.

24:20.806 --> 24:23.900
There's nothing to be afraid of.
After all , we've got
the. . .high ground .

24:23.976 --> 24:25.000
[ Thunder rumbles ]

24:25.077 --> 24:27.375
[ Squeaks ]

24:27.446 --> 24:28.538
[ Rimshot barks ]

24:28.614 --> 24:31.344
Yeah .
Good suggestion , Rimshot.

24:31.416 --> 24:32.849
<i>Why didn't l think of that?</i>

24:32.918 --> 24:35.182
Why don't we go on home?
How 'bout it?

24:35.254 --> 24:37.313
<i>[ Roaring ]</i>

24:37.389 --> 24:40.222
Aah !

24:40.292 --> 24:42.317
Boy, l sure hope
you're from Keebler!

24:42.394 --> 24:45.124
[ Growling ]

24:45.197 --> 24:47.597
You better back off!
You don't want to fight me!

24:47.666 --> 24:49.600
l know tai chi , kung fu ,
Shao-lin .

24:49.668 --> 24:52.296
l saw Hulkamania
three times, once in slow-mo!

24:52.371 --> 24:54.168
[ Growls ]

24:54.239 --> 24:55.638
Back off!
Oh , don't kill me!

24:55.707 --> 24:57.368
Don't kill me!
l don't want to die!

24:57.442 --> 25:00.070
<i>[ Growling ]</i>

25:00.145 --> 25:02.409
[ Stammering ]

25:02.481 --> 25:04.415
[ Growling stops ]

25:04.483 --> 25:06.246
[ Thunder crashes ]

25:06.318 --> 25:10.049
[ Thunder echoing ]

25:10.122 --> 25:12.716
[ Breathing heavily ]

25:12.791 --> 25:14.850
All right.
Civilization .

25:14.927 --> 25:18.419
See you , guys.
l'm already late,
and my mom's gonna kill me.

25:18.497 --> 25:20.465
Yeah . Yeah ,
l'm out of here, too.

25:20.532 --> 25:23.126
Later, dudes.
See y'all tomorrow.

25:23.202 --> 25:26.194
[ Crickets chirp ]

25:33.545 --> 25:34.978
[ Thunder crashes ]

25:35.047 --> 25:37.743
[ Rustling ]

25:37.816 --> 25:40.011
[ Thunder echoing ]

25:45.824 --> 25:47.815
[ Owl hoots ]

25:50.362 --> 25:51.954
[ Bird caws ]

25:52.030 --> 25:53.759
[ Wind blows ]

26:00.372 --> 26:01.805
Aah !

26:01.874 --> 26:04.502
Somebody help me!
Help -- anyone!

26:04.576 --> 26:06.373
[ Grunts ] Help!

26:06.445 --> 26:07.742
Somebody! Ernest!

26:07.813 --> 26:08.905
Help!

26:08.981 --> 26:10.243
[ Grunts ]

26:10.315 --> 26:12.613
Kenny! Elizabeth !
Where are you?

26:12.684 --> 26:15.152
Oh , no!
Oh , help! Come on !

26:15.220 --> 26:17.154
<i>[ Ernest's voice ]</i>
<i>Hey, l got ya.</i>

26:17.222 --> 26:19.850
[ Breathing heavily ]
Thanks, Ernest. You saved me.

26:19.925 --> 26:21.324
l thought l was a goner.

26:21.393 --> 26:25.557
A-a-a-a-a-a-ah !

26:25.631 --> 26:27.121
[ Growls ]

26:29.001 --> 26:31.765
[ Screaming stops ]

26:31.837 --> 26:34.670
[ Evil laughter ]

26:39.278 --> 26:40.210
Sheriff!

26:40.279 --> 26:41.177
[ Thunder crashes ]

26:41.280 --> 26:42.474
Sheriff Binder!

26:42.547 --> 26:44.481
[ Thunder rumbles ]

26:44.549 --> 26:46.915
-- [ Pounding on door ]
-- Sheriff!

26:46.985 --> 26:48.782
Sheriff Binder! Open up!

26:48.854 --> 26:51.084
Aah !
Sheriff Binder, open up, please!

26:51.156 --> 26:52.088
Help!

26:52.157 --> 26:53.749
lt was a monster!
lt was awful !

26:53.825 --> 26:55.349
The tree and the lightning
and --

26:55.427 --> 26:57.952
and it had great, big teeth
and things on its ears like this

26:58.030 --> 27:00.624
and its head was at least
this big and about this long --

27:00.699 --> 27:03.133
<i>Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.</i>
<i>Ernest, slow down.</i>
<i>What happened?</i>

27:03.201 --> 27:04.828
Ernest, do you know
what time it is?

27:04.903 --> 27:07.565
Maybe Old Lady Hackmore was
right -- maybe it <i>was</i> a troll !

27:07.639 --> 27:10.267
Luckily, l was there to beat it
within an inch of its face --

27:10.342 --> 27:12.401
Hold it.
Old Lady Hackmore?

27:12.477 --> 27:15.446
Yeah , the kids and l built
a treehouse out there,
and she got real steamed --

27:15.514 --> 27:17.243
You took Kenny and the kids
out there,

27:17.316 --> 27:18.943
trespassing
on that old lady's land?

27:19.017 --> 27:20.314
Yeah , but what happened?

27:20.385 --> 27:22.512
Sheriff, l saw a troll !
l really saw a troll !

27:22.587 --> 27:25.784
Dad , something really strange
was happening in those woods
tonight.

27:25.857 --> 27:27.950
Yeah , you got to
believe me, sheriff!

27:28.026 --> 27:31.325
Yeah , look, Ernest, whoa.
Listen , you just had
a nightmare, okay?

27:31.396 --> 27:32.556
-- So pinch yourself. . .
-- Ow!

27:32.631 --> 27:34.292
. . .and go on home --

27:34.366 --> 27:36.231
No, l'm not dreaming .
This isn't a nightmare.
That really hurt.

27:36.301 --> 27:38.132
-- We'll talk about it tomorrow.
-- This thing was huge!

27:38.203 --> 27:39.534
lt had this great,
big head --

27:39.604 --> 27:40.764
Good night, Ernest.

27:40.839 --> 27:42.204
lt was probably just --

27:42.274 --> 27:44.265
well , it was more about --
it was about this tall ,

27:44.343 --> 27:46.402
and it looked like a giant,
big Mr. Potato Head ,

27:46.478 --> 27:47.877
only as big
as a watermelon . . .

27:47.946 --> 27:51.541
[ Growling ]

27:51.616 --> 27:53.607
[ Thunder crashes ]

27:57.456 --> 27:59.117
[ Thunder crashes ]

28:02.761 --> 28:05.059
[ Bird hooting ]

28:14.072 --> 28:16.905
[ Wood creaking ]

28:16.975 --> 28:21.173
<i>[ Deep, raspy voice ]</i>
<i>Grow, my children, grow.</i>

28:25.817 --> 28:28.377
[ Thunder rumbles ]

28:28.453 --> 28:30.478
<i>Ernest: Oh, Miss Hackmore!</i>

28:30.555 --> 28:32.580
<i>Miss Hackmore!</i>

28:32.657 --> 28:33.885
l'm sorry to bother you .

28:33.959 --> 28:35.893
You have bothered
the whole planet.

28:35.961 --> 28:38.429
You're cursed , now you're
rubbing it off on me.

28:38.497 --> 28:39.862
But it's about
what you said .

28:39.931 --> 28:42.422
l . . .
l let the troll out.

28:42.501 --> 28:43.763
Uh . . .

28:43.835 --> 28:46.531
That which has been promised
is delivered .

28:46.605 --> 28:48.232
l-lt was huge!

28:48.306 --> 28:51.207
lt had a great, big head and
little, tiny, beady eyes,

28:51.276 --> 28:52.903
and great, big noses!

28:52.978 --> 28:55.276
They were. . .
it was horrible!

28:55.347 --> 28:59.078
You haven't seen horrible
till you see what it does
to the children .

28:59.151 --> 29:01.051
Heaven help us.

29:01.119 --> 29:03.280
Them that dies will be
the lucky ones!

29:03.355 --> 29:04.344
Oh !

29:04.423 --> 29:06.323
[ Metal clangs ]

